&lt;p>The elimination method is when you eliminate one variable, solve for the other one, then solve for the one you eliminated. You can multiply one equation by a number to eliminate a variable. The substitution method is when you substitute a variable with an expression. Personally, I only do substitution if a variable is already isolated.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>